@node "Welcome" "Welcome to Amiga Information Online"

@{fg shine} Welcome@{fg text}

 Welcome to the Christmas edition of Amiga Information Online,
firstly I would like to wish you all a Merry Christmas and
hope you have a great time. Secondly I hope you've wrote
your list ;) hehe as there are a few gems floating around
for the Amiga at them moment and no doubt you'll find a few
or probably many Christmas reductions on various bits and
pieces.

 A new year is just round the corner so lets hope '98 can bring
more cheer to the Amiga scene with the release of a new Workbench
and even hopefully a new Amiga by the end of the year.

 Well as always we've got the latest reviews of everything you've
ever wanted and you MUST get hold of but we've also got reviews
of some of the things that aren't that good so you might want to
avoid downloading them!
 
 This issue is the biggest issue yet and thats to celebrate
Christmas, the next big issue of AIO will be in May '98 when AIO
becomes 1 year old :) The articles section is bursting with thousands
of usful articles for you to read including alot of the Vulcan
web site for you without web (WWW) access and some other interesting
articles like the history and the future of the Amiga and the latest
list of new games planned for these last few days of '97 and the
rest of '98, lets hope all of them get published.

 Well once again I say goodbye and I hope you will join us in January
in the new year. Keep all those letters and christmas messages
comming in and i'll enclude them in the next issue.

                               @{b} Chris Seward - Editor @{ub}

