@node "gr1" "Superballz"

@{fg shine} Superballz@{fg text}

 Superballz is a 'Marble Maddness' sytle game. The idea is to roll
you marble around the screen completing various task like flicking
switch pads and collecting certain objects.

 The game is pretty easy to get the hang of and once you've started
playing you won't want to stop until you have completed that certain
level that you've been trying to complete for ages. There are only
10 levels but it does come with its own level designer so you can
make more challengers for yourself and friends. Although I couldn't
manage to get the editor to work because it just crashed out everytime
I won't comment to much on that but maybe it's because I recived a
faultly version.

 The first level is quite easy, it just envolves flicking a couple of
switches and then rolling up the side of the board to come down round
past the hole and then get to the exit. As you progress though you
find yourself retrying the levels over and over again until you can
complete it. Some of the levels are very crafterly designed and
require some skill to figure out. You can either take the dangerous
choice and just hope you end up at the exit or you can plan out
your route carefully before. The best way is to go slowly otherwise
you find yourself running into spikes or flying off the side of
the board which results in death. There are extra lifes to pick up,
but you have to risk a life to gain another one because they are
placed in places that are hard to get to.

 Overall this game is one of the best P.D. games i've seen in a long
time. Make sure you get it because it will last you for ages without
getting bored, and then theres the insentive to create your own levels
and show the rest of the world your talent by uploading them to something
like the Aminet.

