@node "gr2" "SWOS 97/98"

@{fg shine} SWOS '97/'98 Update@{fg text}

 As a long time player of Sensible Soccer I jump at the chance
to buy every latest updated of the game, when buying SWOS '96/'97
I found out that SWOS was no longer accourding to the box but
in actual fact I found out that there bringing out a game on the
PC and Playstation called SWOS2000 with 3D graphics and commentry.
I was really anoyed about this as it was just a way to make
us Amiga users think that they couldn't do any more to the game
but really they just dumped the Amiga, took our money and run!

 Anyway on with the review. SWOS '96/'97 is as you may know looking
a bit dated with all the transfers that have gone on over the period
from Christmas '96 to nearly Christmas '97 so the nice chaps who
made this have updated all the teams they know of and updated the
screens and pitches to say Sensible World Of Soccer '97/'98.

 All the latest signings are done like Ronaldo at Inter, Petit,
Grimandi and all the other thousands of French signings at Arsenal,
Ince, Owen & Riedle at Liverpool and many more people at all
the different clubs.

 This update does not updated every team but the work, effort and
time that has gone into this deservers to be comended.

 Overall this is a great package, one it is free so you don't have
to fork out £9.99 to Sensible software and two Sensible Software
aren't making any more updates. This is easy to install and makes
the game much better!

