@node "gr3" "6thSense"

@{fg shine} 6th Sense Investigations Preview@{fg text}

 Back in the days when Amiga topped the charts as the best selling
computer and 10 games where comming out practically everyday there
used to be a few Adventure games like the classics Monkey Island
1&2 and the Indiana Jones series of games by Lucas Arts a division
of the Lucas films company owned by George Lucas.

 I have wanted an adventure game for ages now and there has been
a shortage of them as most companys on the Amiga are producing
high spec games to show off the great capabilitys of the amiga,
and thats the way it should be, but there is still the fact that
most of us would still like to play some adventure games.

 Then 6th Sense came along to save my day :) I have only had a
chance to look at the demo version and it seems to be shaping
up quite well, the graphics are not excellently drawn but they
are cartoony and have a funny atmosfere about them which
should keep you entertained through-out the game. In the demo
you can go around various locations doing different things to
get an idea of what the full game will be like. One of the best
things about 6th Sense is that the music is just sooo good and
on the full CD version they have promissed full speech for each
charictor so I can't wait to see that.

 Although 6th Sense isn't as good as some of the older gems of
adventure era it is a different twist and will keep you happiliy
amused for quite a while.

