@node "ur6" "Magnum Chat V1.1"

@{fg shine} Magnum Chat V1.1@{fg text}

 You may have seen the review of Magnum Chat v1.0 last month. Well
already back this month is a new version of it. There have been
alot of improvements which is always a nice thing! A quick rundown
of it first though. MCV1.1 is a Maxs BBS door, it's a replacement
for Max chat. It is a spilt screen chatter like most these days.

 This version there is the option to flick around different styles
of chatter, there have also been some more styles added in like
a Gremlins chat style and a Yaan chat style chatter. The ctrl&l
bug has gone if you pressed that in the last version the whole
screen would clear black. Now when you press ctrl and l the bottom
most part of the screen clears right the way up to the top making
I look pretty fancy. I havn't noticed any other bugs either so
all in all it's still one of the best chatters around.

 The speed of Magnum chat has been improved on massivly since
the last version so you don't have to wait for your text to come
up. The only real problem is that sometimes some of your letters
get cut out when both of you are typing, this may be my fault
but if your low on memory and if you only have a slower processor
then excpect that to happen.

 Overall this version of Magnum Chat is well worth the download,
it isn't better than Yaanchat but it isn't worse either. They both
have there own qualitys. My favourite out of the both is probably
Magnum chat because it is alot less buggy than Yaanchat is this
time around. A nice piece of kit that will cheer your christmas
up no doubt!!!

