@node "ur7" "Envelope"

@{fg shine} Envelope V1.07@{fg text}

 Envelope is a program dedicated to printing addresses on envelopes,
it has been a pain for me in the past when trying to print directly
onto envelopes using programs such as CED and other various text
editors as everytime I used it I would have to test on a piece
of paper where the address would print out each time. So when I
finnally got it right, I found out that the writting would smudge
on the envelope making it unreadable.

 Envelope came to the rescue, one set up and it can be saved forever
so you don't have to set it up each time, it comes with a nice
interface and loads of options to play around with. It is very
easy to set up and you can be printing on envelopes within 1min
of loading it up.

 There are different styles of fonts and things like italic and
bold that you can use which you change at your own leisure.  Once
you have set up the amount the feed down at how far across you
want the address to be you never have to touch it again and then
you can just print atomatically.

 A top notch program and one well worth downloading!!!

